The paper discusses attacks and defenses in both machine learning and digital watermarking, which are subfields of computer security (cs.CR) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper specifically focuses on applications such as face recognition (cs.CV) and malware detection (cs.LG), which are common use cases for machine learning. Additionally, the paper discusses techniques for embedding information in signals, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
